{
  "texts": [
    "Without effectively utilizing such knowledge, LLMs frequently fail to pinpoint the key aspect that contradicts commonsense, leading to inaccurate explanations.To boost LLMs' commonsense explanation ability, in this paper, we propose a Two-stage Identification and Prompting framework (TIP), which reconstructs implicit knowledge to help LLMs generate more accurate and contextually relevant explanations.",
    "Notably, TIP is model-agnostic, making it adaptable to any LLM without any training data.",
    "The framework consisted of two stages.",
    "In the first stage, TIP identifies the nonsensical concepts within the input statements, which are essential for reconstructing implicit knowledge.",
    "These concepts represent words that semantically conflict with commonsense, acting as the core elements responsible for the commonsense contradiction."
  ]
}